article.headline: S. Dakota State 49, Indiana St. 9
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Ryan Berry threw four touchdown passes, including two to Glen Fox, and Kyle Minett ran for two other TDs to lead South Dakota State over Indiana State 49-9 Saturday, extending the Sycamores' losing streak to 22 games. Minett's 1- and 13-yard scoring runs and a Tony Thompson safety gave South Dakota State (4-4, 3-1 Missouri Valley) a 16-0 halftime lead. Fox pulled in Berry scoring passes covering 8 and 39 yards in the third quarter, punctuated by the only touchdown by Indiana State (0-8, 0-4) when a Darrius Gates pass to Jeramie Gray went 42 yards for the score. Berry connected with JaRon Harris over 6 yards and Colin Cochart for 10 yards in the fourth quarter and Ryan Crawford ran 5 yards for the Jackrabbits' other touchdown. South Dakota State piled up 498 offensive yards, led by Berry's 261 yards on 19-of-25 passing. Fox was Berry's favorite target, finishing with seven catches for 83 yards. Minett rushed 21 times for 145 yards and caught four passes for 65 yards. The Jackrabbits sacked Indiana State quarterback Ryan Roberts four times, and Roberts had minus-8 net yards on 25 carries.
